foreFrf8Module.description: This MIB module defines FR/ATM interworking tables. It gives means to create/remove a FR/ATM interworking connection and provides several statistics at connection level.

frf8ConnTable.name: frf8ConnTable
frf8ConnTable.description: Table of cross connections between the frame relay and ATM Fabric connections

frf8ConnEntry.name: frf8ConnEntry
frf8ConnEntry.description: Entry in the frame relay/atm netmod crossconnect table

frf8ConnFrServiceIfIndex.name: frf8ConnFrServiceIfIndex
frf8ConnFrServiceIfIndex.description: Interface index of the Frame Relay service this connection exists on

frf8ConnDlci.name: frf8ConnDlci
frf8ConnDlci.description: DLCI of this connection on the frame relay service

frf8ConnFabServiceIfIndex.name: frf8ConnFabServiceIfIndex
frf8ConnFabServiceIfIndex.description: This is the IfIndex associated with the fabric pseudo atm service this connection is mapped to by the agent when this Frame Relay connection is created. This IfIndex can be converted to a BNP notation value through the ifIndexMapTable of the fore-switch MIB. That BNP value can be used to establish a connection accross the switching fabric by means of the FORE-switch MIB

frf8ConnFabVpi.name: frf8ConnFabVpi
frf8ConnFabVpi.description: This is the fabric VPI(equivalent to ivpi) of the ATM connection this frame relay/ATM connection is mapped to by the agent when this row is created. This VPI will be used to establish a connection accross the switching fabric by means of the FORE-switch MIB

frf8ConnFabVci.name: frf8ConnFabVci
frf8ConnFabVci.description: This is the fabric VCI (equivalent to ivci)of the ATM connection this frame relay connection is mapped to by the agent when this row is created. This VCI will be used to establish a connection accross the switching fabric by means of the FORE-switch MIB

frf8ConnRowStatus.name: frf8ConnRowStatus
frf8ConnRowStatus.description: This object is used for dynamic creation of entries in this table and all frame relay connection level tables. This object is also used to delete existing connection rows.

frf8ConnProfileEpdPpdIndex.name: frf8ConnProfileEpdPpdIndex
frf8ConnProfileEpdPpdIndex.description: The index of the EpdPpd Controller profile which contains: 1 ) Enable/disable the EPD for CLP=0 cells for a specific connection; 2 ) Enable/disable the EPD for CLP=1 cells for a specific connection; 3 ) Enable/disable the PPD for CLP=1 cells for a specific connection.

frf8ConnAtmAddrType.name: frf8ConnAtmAddrType
frf8ConnAtmAddrType.description: Defines the address format of the ATM Service User end point

frf8ConnAtmAddress.name: frf8ConnAtmAddress
frf8ConnAtmAddress.description: The destination ATM address to which this Virtual Circuit is connected.

frf8ConnAtmSubAddrType.name: frf8ConnAtmSubAddrType
frf8ConnAtmSubAddrType.description: Defines the sub-address format of the ATM Service User end point

frf8ConnAtmSubAddress.name: frf8ConnAtmSubAddress
frf8ConnAtmSubAddress.description: The destination ATM subaddress to which this Virtual Circuit is connected.

frf8ConnFrAddrType.name: frf8ConnFrAddrType
frf8ConnFrAddrType.description: Defines the frame relay address format of the Frame Relay Service User end point

frf8ConnFrAddress.name: frf8ConnFrAddress
frf8ConnFrAddress.description: The address to which the Frame Relay DLCI is connected.

frf8ConnAdminStatus.name: frf8ConnAdminStatus
frf8ConnAdminStatus.description: Indicates whether the particular virtual circuit is operational.

frf8ConnOperStatus.name: frf8ConnOperStatus
frf8ConnOperStatus.description: The current operational status of the interworking connection

frf8ConnCreationTime.name: frf8ConnCreationTime
frf8ConnCreationTime.description: The value of sysUpTime when the virtual circuit was created

frf8ConnTimeChange.name: frf8ConnTimeChange
frf8ConnTimeChange.description: The value of sysUpTime (MIB II) when last there was a change in the virtual circuit state

frf8ConnPVCAlarmReason.name: frf8ConnPVCAlarmReason
frf8ConnPVCAlarmReason.description: Defines the reason why the PVC entered/exited the alarmed condition.Defines if the SAC (service affect Condition) is caused/cleared by the Frame Relay network(frAlarmed/frClear), or by the ATM network (aisAlarmed/aisClear,rdiAlarmed/aisClear). The nodefect means no current SAC in either network. This object will be part of the frf8PVCAlarmTRAP.

frf8ConnAtmToFrPDUDiscards.name: frf8ConnAtmToFrPDUDiscards
frf8ConnAtmToFrPDUDiscards.description: The number of PDU's coming from the ATM network to the FR network that are discarded by the interworking function

frf8ConnFrToAtmPDUDiscards.name: frf8ConnFrToAtmPDUDiscards
frf8ConnFrToAtmPDUDiscards.description: The number of PDU's coming from the FR network to the ATM network that are discarded by the interworking function

frf8ConnAtmToFrUnkProts.name: frf8ConnAtmToFrUnkProts
frf8ConnAtmToFrUnkProts.description: The number of PDU's received with an unknown protocol type by the interworking function from the ATM network

frf8ConnFrToAtmUnkProts.name: frf8ConnFrToAtmUnkProts
frf8ConnFrToAtmUnkProts.description: The number of PDU's received with an unknown protocol type by the interworking function from the Frame Relay network

frf8ConnAtmToFrArpNakDiscards.name: frf8ConnAtmToFrArpNakDiscards
frf8ConnAtmToFrArpNakDiscards.description: The number of AAL-5 ARP NAK PDU's that are discarded by the interworking function on this ATM VCC.If the iwf, interworking function receives an ATM ARP with opcode 10 (NAK), the ARP packet is discarde, since FR ARP does not support that opcode.

frf8PVCStatus.name: frf8PVCStatus
frf8PVCStatus.description: This trap indicates when an interworking PVC has experienced an alarmed condition, either on the ATM network side or Frame Relay side. Also it is generated when the PVC alarmed condition is cleared. It carries the opera tional status of the PVC by the frf8ConnOperStatus as well as the reason why exiting,entering or changing the alarmed state frf8ConnPVCAlarmReason. If the interworking PVC changes its status by a AdminStatus command (active/inactive/testing), causing the frf8ConnOperStatus to change (up/down), this trap will be generated with frf8ConnPVCAlarmReason set to 'nodefect'. This TRAP will give the support to manage defects that might occur in either Frame Relay network or ATM network, even if the PVC Operational Status is already down.
